    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="545"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Canada/4337</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Canada</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Riggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-04">June 4,
                            1930</date>.<lb/>[Received June 9.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1443</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In continuation of my despatch No. 1430 of May
                    23, 1930,<note n="8" xml:id="d545fn8">Not printed.</note> and as a conclusion to
                    that and to the series of previous despatches regarding the debate in the
                    Canadian Parliament on Bill No. 15, entitled “An Act to Amend the Export Act”, I
                    have the honor to report that this Bill received the Royal assent, and
                    consequently became law, at the final session of Parliament on May 30, 1930.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">B. Reath Riggs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
